{"author":{"id":"8db7cfd50e1e91dacc00581ae889d9f9a6b1aad44cc6367afa71706301df22d3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1704842587,"nonce":"y7Du9G0MxiFofnXP05og9f30mHs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s57lHVO","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5702","origin":"github"},"title":"Help with the assign_primary_output attribute of the discover_datasets tag","message":"Can someone help me understand how the `assign_primary_output` attribute of `discover_datasets` works?\n\nFrom reading the [Tool XML File docs](https://docs.galaxyproject.org/en/master/dev/schema.html#tool-outputs-data-discover-datasets) I am expecting a single dataset (the discovered one) if I set `assign_primary_output=\"true\"`\n\n\u003e Replace the primary dataset described by the parameter data parameter with the first output discovered.\n\nHowever, I always get two datasets. Here's an example:\n\n```xml\n\u003ctool id=\"test_discover_replace\" name=\"Test discover and replace\" profile=\"20.01\" version=\"0.0.1\"\u003e\n    \u003ccommand\u003e\u003c![CDATA[\n        mkdir outputs \u0026\u0026 \n        echo \"file 1\" \u003e\u003e outputs/normalfile.ext \u0026\u0026\n        echo \"file_2\" \u003e\u003e outputs/Genus_species.txt\n    ]]\u003e\u003c/command\u003e\n    \u003cinputs\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"tf\" label=\"True or False\" type=\"boolean\" checked=\"true\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/inputs\u003e\n    \u003coutputs\u003e\n        \u003cdata name=\"regular_ds\" label=\"Normal data tag\" format=\"txt\" from_work_dir=\"outputs/normalfile.ext\"/\u003e\n        \u003cdata name=\"discovered_ds\" label=\"${tool.name} discovered dataset\" format=\"txt\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiscover_datasets pattern=\"(?P\u0026lt;designation\u0026gt;.+)\\.txt\" directory=\"outputs\" format=\"txt\" recurse=\"false\" assign_primary_output=\"true\" visible=\"true\"/\u003e\n            \u003cfilter\u003etf\u003c/filter\u003e\n        \u003c/data\u003e\n    \u003c/outputs\u003e\n\u003c/tool\u003e\n\n```\n\nHere's the result: I get the discovered file, and an empty dataset (0 lines):\n\n[\n![screenshot-localhost_9090-2024 01 10-10_12_12](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/assets/5971975/8fd0044d-a441-4d81-b248-d36d90c7a8f0)\n](url)\n\nIf I set `visible=\"false\"` I just get the empty dataset.\n\nThis is Galaxy version 23.1.4.dev0 which I'm running with planemo version 0.75.19\n\nThanks for reading!","files":null}]}